This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on January 23, 2017. The memorandum announces the withdrawal of the United States from the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) negotiations and agreement. It states that the administration's policy is to represent the American people and their financial well-being, particularly the American worker, and to create fair and economically beneficial trade deals. The memorandum directs the United States Trade Representative to withdraw the country as a signatory to the TPP and to permanently withdraw from TPP negotiations. Instead, the administration intends to pursue bilateral trade negotiations with individual countries to promote American industry, protect American workers, and raise American wages. The memorandum also authorizes the publication of this directive in the Federal Register.